Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 19:40:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: auto-resolve custom-model-data target texture

When an OverrideEntry has custom_model_data set, walk the loaded resource
packs to follow item model -> overrides[predicate.custom_model_data] ->
custom model -> textures.layer0 (with parent fallback) and use the
resolved texture id. This makes textures attach to the actual custom
model (e.g. a regeneration staff) instead of the bare vanilla item.

- Add ModelTextureResolver that reads model JSONs through ResourcePack
  APIs (no disk scanning) and caches results.
- ORMResourcePack now takes the existing pack list and resolves the
  target identifier per entry: explicit `target` > auto-resolve via
  CMD > vanilla item texture fallback.
- MixinResourceManager forwards the in-flight pack list so the resolver
  sees every pack loaded before ORM.
- ORMConfigManager now persists/loads the existing `target` field.

Co-Authored-By: Devin AI <158243242+devin-ai-integration[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
